Le stylez: @icontips

So while I was reflecting on 2022, I was like did I love it tho?! I mean, my business faltered somewhere between June & September and it had me down for a lil bit, then I realized, SIS, look what all you accomplished this year and the fun that was had.....
1) I launched my very first online makeup course (S/o to @candacesheppard , you are the GOAT and I love you 😘)!
2) I booked paid promotions with large brands 
3)  I met a lot of amazing new clients that I hope to see in the new year
4) My work graced the face of @deborahjoywinans on a billboard in Times Square
5) My Ambuler booked me some incredible makeup moments this year (I love me some you @msamberpriley , truly 😘)
6) I traveled to 7 countries and had the time of my life 🥳
7) I’ve decided to say goodbye to facials while ushering in a new and exciting service (Stay Tuned) (More Details Below)
8) I got to live, love and laugh w/ my freakin amazing friends and family 
9)  I have my health 🙌🏽
10) I’m stepping into my 40th year of life & 20th year as an mua 😳 and I’m excited for all that God has in store for the kid 🤸🏽‍♀️! 
Blessings on Blessings on Blessings!!!
______________________________
Facial Clients:

I love you and thank you for your support, but it’s time to launch something new that doesn’t involve a steamer and extractions 🙈.......but because I like you, I’m leaving you in the hands of @skinbydomonique who is an incredible esty and will have your skin looking like new. Her books are pretty full, so run, don’t walk to her website to book! Domonique save me a facial sis 😩🙏🏽.
______________________________
All other esthetic services remain.......brow waxing, laminiation, tint, body waxing (except the vajay, I literally can’t 🥴), makeup, weddings and 1+1 tutorials.....can’t want to launch this new service, give me 4 weeks!!
See y’all in 2023!

1 week ago today I came home from the most amazing birthday trip ever. Here’s 9 days, 2 countries, 1 train ride and some good shopping, in 90 seconds.
___________
Great travel is 20% destination, 20% accommodations, 10% what you do and 50% who you do it with.....the 7 of us had thee most fun exploring London and Paris, doing whatever and eating whatever. 
My bestfriend @travelwithscott flew in from FL, my 2 bestfriends @tanyaamey & @mikeameynam flew in from Africa, my brother @fredpricejr and sister @mrsangelprice left the pulpit for 2 Sundays (sorry not sorry CCC fam 😜) and my Jen Jen @smiliegin took off work to celebrate a new decade with me, I’m blessed, end of story 💁🏽‍♀️
___________
I added info in my highlights about the trip (i.e. restaurants, accommodations and transportation) for those traveling to either place anytime soon. Toodles ✌🏽.
